Key Match Events: Danish defender Patrick Dorgu scored in the eighty-second minute to make it 1-0.
Swiss defender Nico Elvedi received a red card in the fifty-second minute.
Swiss midfielder Granit Xhaka received Switzerland’s second red card of the match.
Danish midfielder Pierre-Emile Høgbjerg sealed the victory with a goal 2 minutes into stoppage time to make it 2-0.
Pre-Game Insights: Danish supporter Carl expressed high hopes for his team in this year’s Nations League and believed Christian Eriksen would be the most impressive player despite his age.
